## Rollback Procedures

### Automatic Rollback Triggers

**Immediate rollback if:**
- Health check fails (HTTP 500+ status)
- Smoke test fails
- Error rate > 2x baseline
- Critical service unavailable
- Database migration fails with data loss risk

### Rollback Execution

**Kubernetes Rollback:**

```
FUNCTION execute_kubernetes_rollback(deployment_name, namespace):
    Report: "Executing Kubernetes rollback..."

    # Rollback to previous revision
    Bash(command=f"kubectl rollout undo deployment/{deployment_name} --namespace={namespace}")

    # Wait for rollback to complete
    Bash(command=f"kubectl rollout status deployment/{deployment_name} --namespace={namespace} --timeout=5m")

    # Verify rollback success
    rollback_status = parse_kubectl_status()

    IF rollback_status == "success":
        Report: "✓ Kubernetes rollback successful"
    ELSE:
        CRITICAL: "Kubernetes rollback failed - manual intervention required"
```

**Azure App Service Rollback:**

```
FUNCTION execute_azure_rollback(app_name, resource_group):
    Report: "Executing Azure App Service rollback..."

    # Swap staging/production slots back
    Bash(command=f"az webapp deployment slot swap --slot staging --name {app_name} --resource-group {resource_group} --target-slot production --action=swap")

    Report: "✓ Azure App Service rollback successful"
```

**AWS ECS Rollback:**

```
FUNCTION execute_ecs_rollback(cluster, service, previous_task_def):
    Report: "Executing AWS ECS rollback..."

    # Revert to previous task definition
    Bash(command=f"aws ecs update-service --cluster {cluster} --service {service} --task-definition {previous_task_def}")

    # Wait for service stability
    Bash(command=f"aws ecs wait services-stable --cluster {cluster} --services {service}")

    Report: "✓ AWS ECS rollback successful"
```

**Database Rollback:**

```
FUNCTION execute_database_rollback(migration_id, backup_id):
    Report: "Executing database rollback..."

    IF migration_applied:
        # Run down migration
        TRY:
            Bash(command=f"./scripts/rollback_migration.sh {migration_id}")
            Report: "✓ Database migration rolled back"
        EXCEPT:
            WARN: "Migration rollback failed - may need manual intervention"

    IF backup_id AND severe_data_changes:
        # Restore from backup (last resort)
        AskUserQuestion:
        Question: "Database migration rollback failed. Restore from backup?"
        Header: "Database restore"
        Description: "WARNING: This will restore database to pre-deployment state (data loss)"
        Options:
          - label: "Yes - Restore from backup (data loss accepted)"
            description: "Restore database to backup point"
          - label: "No - Manual intervention required"
            description: "DBA will manually resolve migration issues"
        multiSelect: false

        IF answer == "Yes":
            Bash(command=f"./scripts/restore_database.sh {backup_id}")
            Report: "✓ Database restored from backup"
```

### Post-Rollback Actions

```
# Update story status
Edit(file_path=f"devforgeai/specs/Stories/{story_id}.story.md",
     old_string="status: Releasing",
     new_string="status: QA Approved")

# Document rollback
rollback_report = f"""# Rollback: {version}

**Reason:** {rollback_reason}
**Rolled Back At:** {current_timestamp()}
**Previous Version Restored:** {previous_version}

## Root Cause
{rollback_details}

## Actions Taken
- Production rolled back to {previous_version}
- Database restored: {backup_id if backup_id else "N/A"}
- Alerts cleared
- Monitoring resumed

## Impact
- Downtime: {calculate_downtime()}
- Affected Users: {estimate_affected_users()}
- Data Loss: {data_loss_assessment}

## Next Steps
- [ ] Root cause analysis
- [ ] Fix issue in development
- [ ] Re-run QA validation
- [ ] Plan re-deployment
"""

Write(file_path=f"devforgeai/releases/rollback-{version}.md", content=rollback_report)

# Create hotfix story if needed
AskUserQuestion:
Question: "Rollback complete. Create hotfix story for the issue?"
Header: "Hotfix creation"
Description: "Create new story to track fix and re-deployment"
Options:
  - label: "Yes - Create hotfix story"
    description: "Create HOTFIX-XXX story for expedited fix"
  - label: "No - Fix in next sprint"
    description: "Address in normal sprint workflow"
multiSelect: false

IF answer == "Yes":
    # Invoke orchestration to create hotfix story
    Skill(command="devforgeai-orchestration --create-story --type=hotfix --parent={story_id}")
```

