## Integration Points

### From devforgeai-qa

**Handoff Data Required:**
- Story ID with status "QA Approved"
- QA report with PASS status (devforgeai/qa/reports/{story-id}-qa-report.md)
- Test coverage metrics (must meet 95%/85%/80% thresholds)
- Zero critical/high violations

**Validation:**
```
# This skill MUST validate QA approval before proceeding
IF story.status != "QA Approved":
    BLOCK: "Story not QA approved"
    Action: "Run devforgeai-qa --mode=deep first"

IF NOT file_exists(qa_report):
    BLOCK: "QA report missing"
    Action: "QA validation required"
```

### To devforgeai-orchestration

**Updates Provided:**
- Story status changed to "Released"
- Workflow history updated with release details
- Sprint progress updated (if story part of sprint)
- Release notes path

**Orchestration Then:**
- Marks story as complete
- Updates sprint velocity
- May trigger next story in queue

---

## Success Criteria

**Release skill succeeds when ALL criteria met:**

- [x] QA approval validated (story status + report)
- [x] Staging deployment successful
- [x] Staging smoke tests passed
- [x] Production deployment successful (using selected strategy)
- [x] Production smoke tests passed
- [x] Metrics within acceptable thresholds (< 1.2x baseline)
- [x] Release notes generated
- [x] Story status updated to "Released"
- [x] Changelog updated
- [x] Sprint progress updated
- [x] Post-release monitoring configured
- [x] No rollback required

**Output Artifacts:**
- Release notes: `devforgeai/releases/release-{version}.md`
- Updated story document: `devforgeai/specs/Stories/{story-id}.story.md` (status = "Released")
- Updated changelog: `CHANGELOG.md`
- Deployment logs
- Post-release monitoring configuration
- Post-release review task

**Failure Handling:**
- Rollback executed if any validation fails
- Rollback report generated: `devforgeai/releases/rollback-{version}.md`
- Story status reverted to "QA Approved"
- Hotfix story optionally created

